text.section:
Certificates issued on the lives of individuals below the society's minimum age for adult membership:
may provide for transfer of control of ownership to the insured at an age specified in the certificate;
may require approval of an application for membership in order to effect the transfer;
may provide in all other respects for the regulation, government, and control of the certificate and all rights, obligations, and liabilities incident to and connected with the certificate; and
shall specify ownership rights to the certificate prior to any transfer of the certificate.
